
IRCUtils is a Python framework for communicating with the  IRC protocol.
It's designed for ease of use for anything you'd need. It also has fast 
and simple support for writing IRC bots.

This branch represents a complete rewrite and totally new architecture,
utilizing Python 3's new asynchronous programming features.


Roadmap:
========

v. 0.4.0 -- basic client functionality: connect, user, nick, ping
v. 0.5.0 -- more client functionality
v. 1.0.0 -- same level of functionality as original ircutils
v. 2.0.0 -- full client spec
v. 3.0.0 -- Some server functionality